  "prompt": "How much should I aim in my graduation to get into IIM A/B/C assuming I get a 99+ percentile in CAT?",
  "response": "To increase your chances of getting into IIM Ahmedabad (IIM A), IIM Bangalore (IIM B), or IIM Calcutta (IIM C) with a 99+ percentile in CAT, it is important to aim for a strong academic record in your graduation. While the exact minimum requirements can vary slightly each year, usually due to changes in the weightage given to different components, here are some guidelines based on historical trends and typical criteria used by these institutes:\n\n1. **Graduation Scores**:\n   - Aim to achieve at least a 70-75% or above (7-7.5 out of 10 CGPA) in your graduation. While some candidates with lower percentages have been accepted, higher graduation scores can significantly improve your chances.\n   - Adherence to specific academic cut-offs can be important. For certain programs and categories, specific minimum thresholds may be set.\n\n2. **Class 10th and 12th Scores**:\n   - High scores in your 10th and 12th standard exams (often above 80-85%) are also desirable, as these scores are usually considered during the shortlisting and selection processes.\n\n3. **Profile Considerations**:\n   - Overall academic consistency is key. Higher percentages across all levels (10th, 12th, graduation) strengthen your profile.\n   - Work experience (if applicable) can add weight to your application. Ideally, relevant and impactful work experience of 1-3 years post-graduation can be beneficial.\n   - Extra-curricular activities, leadership roles, and other achievements can further enhance your application.\n\n4. **Category-specific Considerations**:\n   - Be aware of the specific cut-offs for different categories (General, NC-OBC, SC/ST, PwD). Category-specific reservations can impact the percentile and GPA requirements.\n\n5. **Selection Criteria**:\n   - Performance in CAT is crucial, but so is the academic profile, performance in the written ability test (WAT), group discussion (GD), and personal interview (PI).\n\nTo sum up, while the CAT percentile is a critical factor, ensuring a robust academic record throughout your education, coupled with diverse achievements and relevant experience, makes your application more competitive. Aim high in all aspects to maximize your chances of gaining admission to IIM A/B/C.",
